1.title: Episode #4.1
1.plot: Glenn (Jack Yang) is arrested in the Philippines on suspicion of murder. Cheong is assigned to take charge of Team Epsilon and the team welcomes ASP Sophie Thomas (Liv Lo) as they investigate a nightclub with illegal immigrants as hostesses. DSP Victor de Cruz (Desmond Tan) returns to join CID Intel after his overseas studies and has a special interest in Glenn's case. Glenn turns fugitive when he escapes from the police, but the police and Miguel's men close in on him, Glenn is left with little choice but to seek refuge with a dangerous ally.

2.title: Episode #4.2
2.plot: Glenn (played by Jack Yang) has joined the Multo syndicate in the Philippines and he is tasked to oversee a smuggling operation into Singapore. Team Epsilon probes into a family suspected of harbouring illegal immigrants and uncovers a dark secret.

3.title: Episode #4.3
3.plot: The team investigates the mysterious circumstances surrounding an over stayer student's disappearance. Analyn played by Bela Ocampo arrives in Singapore to further her studies, and turns to Glenn for help when she's cheated of her money by an agent.

4.title: Episode #4.4
4.plot: Amidst questions about Cheong and Dynesh's encounter with Glenn, Team Epsilon investigates the sudden disappearance of a domestic helper who steals her employers passport. Anton decides to put Glenn's loyalty to the test. Matthew challenges Dynesh to be honest with himself and his feelings towards Sophie and Cheong's life is turned upside down by the arrival of an unexpected visitor.

5.title: Episode #4.5
5.plot: When female drug mules are caught at the checkpoints smuggling heroin in sanitary pads, Team Epsilon goes undercover to nab a syndicate thats dealing drugs at a Full Moon party. Glenn learns how Anton takes instructions from his higher-ups and Cheong is in a dilemma about his past and worries about how it would affect his family.

6.title: Episode #4.6
6.plot: When female drug mules are caught at the checkpoints smuggling heroin in sanitary pads, Team Epsilon goes undercover to nab a syndicate thats dealing drugs at a Full Moon party. Glenn learns how Anton takes instructions from his higher-ups and Cheong is in a dilemma about his past and worries about how it would affect his family.

7.title: Episode #4.7
7.plot: A sociopath teen bully hires a man to rape a girl. Team Epsilon goes on the trail of a suspected illegal immigrant but something doesn't match up. Meanwhile, Glenn tries to uncover more info on Multo but things take a drastic turn as Anton comes to a realization about Glenn and decides to eliminate him.

8.title: One of Us
8.plot: The team investigates the case of a tampered passport as it burgeons into maid abuse and manslaughter. Victor from CID pursues Glenn as a prime suspect for murder, but Glenn refuses to surrender. Kara and Team Epsilon try to clear his name.

9.title: Episode #4.9
9.plot: A recent increase in fraudulent marriages spurs the team to action. Glenn is back as the head of Team Epsilon, but concerns about Multo continue to occupy his thoughts. In the Philippines, Multo plans their next move.

10.title: Doctor No
10.plot: The discovery of an illegal immigrant with a missing kidney sparks off an investigation into an organ-stealing syndicate. Matthew faces family pressures and has doubts about staying in ICA. Glenn and Kara are at a crossroads in their relationship and it looks to be taking a positive turn or ...not.

11.title: BFF
11.plot: The team's investigation of a missing foreign worker leads to a grisly find at Bedok Reservoir. Tensions between Glenn and Kara continue to rise over his inability to express his true feelings. Norah rejoins the team after a long absence. Glenn finally confirms a worrying suspicion he's had all along.

12.title: Episode #4.12
12.plot: Team Epsilon goes undercover to flush out a scheme involving impersonating ICA officers to extort money from tourists. A new highly-addictive drug surfaces in Singapore. Meanwhile, Glenn takes steps to keep track of his target - the Leader of Multo.

13.title: Episode #4.13
13.plot: The team is alerted when an overstayer attempts to leave the country using someone else's passport, but the trail leads them to a disturbing discovery. Kara's father is hospitalized for a heart operation, and Glenn tries to be supportive which rouses Analyn's jealousy. Multo looks to make a big move into Singapore. Will they be able to slip past the authorities unnoticed?

1.title: Point of Entry
1.plot: When the leader of Team Epsilon is assassinated in cold blood, Glenn Chua (Carl Ng) is brought in to head this elite ICA task force specializing in intelligence and criminal syndicates consisting of dedicated sniper Vivian de Cruz (Pamlyn Chee), grizzled old-timer Cheong Guan Meng (Bernard Tan), IT extraordinaire Norah Rahmat (Fadhilah) and traceur athlete Dynesh Krishnan (Devarajan). He also reunites with old friend Jackson Goh (Jourdan Lee) in a chance encounter while on the case.

2.title: Arms Race
2.plot: A stabbing case at Glenn and Jackson's old secondary school leads to an unexpected case of smuggled flick knives in Singapore. But when the trail grows cold, there's only one alternative - for Dynesh to go undercover with his old parkour buddies and infiltrate them long enough to discover who's behind this latest case. But Dynesh is just a rookie, will he be able to crack this case or will his inexperience blow his cover - and his life?

3.title: Natural Selection
3.plot: When a shipment of smuggled snakes go awry, Team Epsilon is alerted to the existence of a black market for endangered animals - and a new smuggling operation underway. But when conventional methods fail to catch this smuggler, they must figure out another way to stop him, a way that involves Glenn and Vivian posing as... a couple? Will they be able to outwit the animal smuggler and break this rare species black market?

4.title: Family Ties
4.plot: A midnight raid Police Coast Guard raid turns up a group of illegal immigrants - but where has the middleman gone? A hunt for the middleman ensues, but little does Team Epsilon know - the Angel syndicate is also on the hunt for the middleman. Will they be able to get to the middleman before Angel does, or will he end up a victim of the very smuggling ring he was a part of?

5.title: Adult Toy Story
5.plot: There's more than meets the eye to Norah's auntie's new boyfriend. Meanwhile, Glenn starts receiving anonymous tip offs about various smuggled goods - but can he trust the sender? Who is behind these anonymous tip offs, and will Norah be able to uncover the secret behind her auntie's new boyfriend before something disastrous happens?

6.title: Truth and Consequences
6.plot: A lost IC belonging to a man with a wife and job seems perfectly normal until Team Epsilon discovers that the man is mentally challenged and the wife is actually from China! Meanwhile, Glenn and Marianne (Melody Chen) wrestle with the decision to tell his mother that they've gotten a divorce. Will they admit that their marriage has gone south, and will the team be able to find who exactly is behind the recent spate of sham marriages?

7.title: On Angel's Wings
7.plot: A lost IC belonging to a man with a wife and job seems perfectly normal until Team Epsilon discovers that the man is mentally challenged and the wife is actually from China! Meanwhile, Glenn and Marianne (Melody Chen) wrestle with the decision to tell his mother that they've gotten a divorce. Will they admit that their marriage has gone south, and will the team be able to find who exactly is behind the recent spate of sham marriages?

8.title: Child's Play
8.plot: Team Epsilon is called into play when a group of five illegal immigrants are found stranded at the airport. The catch?They're all children. Meanwhile, Joe, the notorious Angel syndicate leader, is now behind bars, but can they get him to confess to his crimes and bring down the syndicate? And who is behind this latest spate of child smuggling?

9.title: Nightswimming
9.plot: When a drug overdose case leads to a new drug smuggling operation in Singapore, Team Epsilon must break this new ring and prevent the Angel syndicate from establishing a foothold in Singapore. Meanwhile, Cheong's old friend becomes an unlikely suspect for drug smuggling. Can he get to the bottom of the matter, and can Team Epsilon stop the Angel syndicate's newest operation?

10.title: My Sister's Keeper
10.plot: A trip to Malaysia turns sour for four old ladies when they become the unsuspecting targets of a pair of Malaysian smugglers. Worst of all, one of them is Cheong's old friend! Meanwhile, Noi (Dusita Anitchitchanchai) comes closer to finding out who murdered Edmund. Will Cheong and Team Epsilon be able to rescue the old ladies from the smugglers before events take a tragic turn?

11.title: Web of Lies
11.plot: When a corpse is found floating in a pool, what turns out to be a routine investigation gets Team Epsilon drawn into a complex web of lies, betrayal, and deceit. Can they unravel this tangled web before the killer escapes? Also, a startling new change comes over the Angel syndicate - a change that does not bode well for our heroes.

12.title: A Crisis of Credit
12.plot: A spate of credit fraud leads Team Epsilon on a hunt for the pair of immigrants who are behind the case, while trying to figure out just who they're working for. Meanwhile, Noi comes to terms with the identity of her lover's killer - her own brother, Ricky (Artikant Noonpukdee), with the help of Jackson. Will our team be able to nab the culprits before they strike again?

13.title: On the Smoking Trail
13.plot: A cigarette bust tips Team Epsilon off to a fast growing cigarette smuggling operation - with one hitch. Who are the runners for them? Meanwhile, Vivian's younger brother runs afoul of bad company. Will she be able to protect her sibling before he goes astray, and will our heroes be able to bust this cigarette smuggling operation before it spirals out of control?

14.title: Mind the Gap
14.plot: The autopsy of a mysterious death of a traveller at Changi Airport turns out to be a severe drug overdose when her heroin levels are 400 times higher than regular overdose cases! And when this turns out to be a new Angel syndicate initiative, can Team Epsilon stop them before more victims are claimed?

15.title: The Gathering Storm
15.plot: Team Epsilon faces their biggest human smuggling case yet when the dead body of an illegal immigrant turns up in the middle of Little India. Meanwhile, Glenn's vacation in Thailand turns into an Angel syndicate investigation... and attack! Will Glenn be able to survive Angel's latest onslaught, and will Team Epsilon be able to bust this latest human smuggling case without Glenn's help?

16.title: Friend or Enemy
16.plot: When a pair of dead bodies are found in a barge, Team Epsilon must find the Angel syndicate connection before more victims fall prey to their latest smuggling operation! Meanwhile, Glenn grows more disillusioned with Team Epsilon and more convinced of Jackson's point of view. Will Glenn be able to retain his faith in the team - or will he be lured to the dark side?

17.title: Sins of the Father
17.plot: The return of one of Singapore's most wanted criminals leads Jackson to discover just how the Angel syndicate was founded. In the mean time, Epsilon makes several discoveries of their own, including a plot to murder an innocent woman and her family. Can they stop the criminal in time, and how will Jackson make use of this latest piece of information in his plans?

18.title: Binary
18.plot: When the Tuas Checkpoint's Protective and Analytic Facility is activated by a chemical spill, the trail leads to an illegal immigrant who also happens to be a terrorist! Meanwhile, Team Epsilon's investigation of Angel leads to a startling conclusion - that Glenn has been bribed? Has Glenn been framed, and will Team Epsilon stop the terrorist before she claims more lives?

19.title: False Faces
19.plot: Angel syndicate initiates an operation that could change the face of smuggling forever - by duplicating biometric passports! Meanwhile Glenn has switched sides, and is now working with Jackson for Angel. Will Team Epsilon be able to foil Angel's plot before Singapore's border security is compromised, and is Glenn really willing to sell out the team to Jackson?

20.title: Endgame
20.plot: Jackson is on the cusp of taking over the Angel syndicate and planning his biggest operation yet, and with Glenn's help, it looks like he just might succeed! It's the final showdown between Team Epsilon and the Angel syndicate. Will Team Epsilon be able to defeat the combined efforts of Glenn and Jackson? Find out in the exciting conclusion to Point of Entry!

1.title: Karma
1.plot: Six months after foiling Angel syndicate, Glenn now has to deal with a tough new boss, Calvin Wong (MARCUS MOK), as well as Kara Yeo (JAYMEE ONG), a Home Team liaison as headstrong as himself. But with Vivian on a study hiatus, Team Epsilon will need all the help they can get when a sham marriage leads to a prostitute with a dangerous agenda.

2.title: Transplanted
2.plot: Liu Ai Ling (JADE SEAH) from CNB and Matthew Yong (DARRYL YONG) from the checkpoints join Team Epsilon. Matthew clashes with Dynesh while Glenn is hesitant to trust Ai Ling. Meanwhile, Team Epsilon's investigation of the death of a China national uncovers a startling secret - an illegal organ transplant.

3.title: Bloodline
3.plot: An abandoned baby leads to the discovery of a runaway Indonesian maid. Team Epsilon discovers in order to crack it, the most unlikely member of their team must go undercover - Norah.

4.title: Fast Girls
4.plot: When the severed head of a PRC woman is found at a rubbish dump, the trail leads to a prostitution ring and Ai Ling must go undercover to infiltrate the group. But how far must she go as a prostitute in order to catch the killer?

5.title: Runner
5.plot: The corpse of a Taiwanese leads to a case of a loansharking ring. But as Team Epsilon discovers, the new face of loansharking is a much younger and more innocent one.

6.title: One Way Ticket
6.plot: A false air ticket brings Team Epsilon to several exploited Filipina overstayers. But the victims are not as helpless as they sound. Meanwhile, Norah's burgeoning friendship to Rohan leads to an unexpected conclusion.

7.title: Child's Play
7.plot: Noi prepares to make a life changing decision, and Glenn goes to Thailand to investigate - only to find that unexpected help has tagged along. Meanwhile, Team Epsilon investigates a case of child smuggling based in Batam.

8.title: Chasing the Dragon Pt.1
8.plot: The latest case of drug smuggling - heroin smuggled in the deep wounds of drug runners - sees Dynesh going into deep cover to find out the mastermind behind the operation.

9.title: Chasing the Dragon Pt. 2
9.plot: While undercover in a sinister drug smuggling ring, Dynesh finds himself coming closer and closer to crossing the line. Will Team Epsilon be able to locate the mastermind before Dynesh loses himself in his cover identity?

10.title: The Devil Inside
10.plot: The double suicide of teen cultists sends Team Epsilon on the trail of a passport smuggling ring. Meanwhile, Dynesh struggles with his drug rehabilitation. In Thailand, Noi grows suspicious of her newly wed husband, Samak.

11.title: Sex, Lies & CCTV
11.plot: A charge of sexual harassment is levied against the most unexpected member of Team Epsilon, even as they investigate a case of passport smuggling. Noi deals with the grief of her father's death, and discovers something unexpected - was he murdered?

12.title: Prickly Heat
12.plot: A desperate madman with a syringe of HIV positive blood is on the loose, and Team Epsilon must stop him before he strikes again. Noi finally embraces her marriage with her husband, Samak - the new leader of Angel syndicate.

13.title: The Good Samaritan
13.plot: Team Epsilon investigates a new passport forgery ring. Meanwhile, Ai Ling faces trouble closer to home, a slasher in her neighbourhood - and she's determined to stop him. They soon find out that the slasher is the key to stopping these passport smugglers.

14.title: Pest Control
14.plot: A case of illegal foreign workers working at a chain of hawker stalls has Team Epsilon stumped - what does it have to do with a China national and a Singaporean? Noi discovers a leak in Angel syndicate, and takes ruthless measures to stop it.

15.title: The Gentle Giant
15.plot: Team Epsilon investigates a most unexpected drug smuggler - a naïve teenager from Nigeria. Vivian comes back to Singapore with a surprise in tow, prompting Noi to return to Singapore as well.

16.title: Lineage
16.plot: Team Epsilon investigates a baby smuggling ring. But solving this case will be difficult when a mysterious assailant also begins targetting their personal lives - especially since there might be a traitor in their ranks.

17.title: Trust
17.plot: Team Epsilon must foil a terrorist plot to bomb Singapore and rescue Vivian's baby from Noi. Ai Ling faces a difficult personal decision as well.

imdb.title: Point of Entry
synopsis:
Point of Entry, the highest-rated one hour drama on Ch 5 in the last 3 years is back by popular demand for a second season, with more riveting real-life inspired cases that have kept Singaporean viewers glued to their TV sets and set Netizens talking on forums.
Core members of the team leader Glenn Chua (CARL NG), veteran Cheong Guan Meng (BERNARD TAN), sharpshooter Vivian De Cruz (PAMELYN CHEE), tech expert Norah Rahmat (FADHILAH SAMSUDIN) and parkour expert Dynesh Krishnan (DEVARAJAN VARADARAJAN) are joined by new members, martial arts expert Liu Ai Ling (JADE SEAH) and gungho, charming Matthew Yong (DARRYL YONG), as well as their newly-appointed politically-savvy boss Calvin Wong (MARCUS MOK) and ambitious go-getter Home Team liaison Kara Yeo (JAYMEE ONG). Noi (DUSITA ANUCHITCHANCHAI), stoic sister of last seasons villain, Jackson (JOURDAN LEE), also makes an unexpected return. How will these characters pose new and intriguing challenges for Team Epsilon?In its second season, Point of Entry continues to feature true life cases that educate and entertain. Viewers will gain invaluable insights through the cases of Team Epsilon, learning how the different components of the Home Team CNB, Police, ICA, etc. work together to ensure Singapore is kept safe and realize that their safety and security is not to be taken for granted.
